[The information regarding clinical signs is somewhat vague. However, if
lips and mouths are turning blue, it may be an indication of a toxicant,
such as nitrate/nitrite, which turns the blood dark and renders it unable
to adequately carry oxygen. Clinical signs of nitrite poisoning may include
intense cyanosis, nausea, dizziness, vomiting, collapse, spasms of
abdominal pain, rapid heart beat, irregular breathing, coma, convulsions,
and death due to circulatory collapse. The estimated lethal dose is 1 to 2
grams. - Mod.TG]
